<style>
    .funder-row {padding: 1em;}
    .funder-logo {width: 160px}
</style>

<h1>SEEK Funding details</h1>

<p>
  SEEK is developed as a component of the <%= link_to "FAIRDOM", "http://fair-dom.org", :target => "_blank" %> project,
  which is funded by the following agencies ...
</p>
<br/>

<div class='row funder-row'>
  <div class='col-md-2'>
  <%= image 'funder-bbsrc',:class=>'funder-logo' %>
  </div>
  <div>
    <%= link_to 'Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council (BBSRC)', 'http://www.bbsrc.ac.uk/', :target => "_blank" %>
    is a UK Research Council and non-departmental public
    body. Being the largest UK public funder of non-medical bioscience, the organization funds scientific research
    institutes and university research departments in the UK.
  </div>
</div>

<div class='row funder-row'>
  <div class='col-md-2'>
    <%= image 'funder-bmbf',:class=>'funder-logo' %>
  </div>
  <div>
    <%= link_to 'The Federal Ministry of Education and Research (Bundesministerium für Bildung und Forschung – BMBF)', 'https://www.bmbf.de/en/', :target => "_blank" %>
    , is a
    cabinet-level ministry of the Federal Republic of Germany. The Ministry provides funding for research projects and
    institutions and sets general educational policy
  </div>
</div>

<div class='row funder-row'>
  <div class='col-md-2'>
    <%= image 'funder-nwo',:class=>'funder-logo' %>
  </div>
  <div>
    <%= link_to 'The Netherlands Organization for Scientific Research (Nederlandse Organisatie voor Wetenschappelijk Onderzoek)', 'http://www.nwo.nl/en', :target => "_blank" %>
    is
    the national research council of the Netherlands. Promoting quality and innovation in science, the organization
    funds
    thousands of top researchers at universities/institutes inside the country.
  </div>
</div>

<div class='row funder-row'>
  <div class='col-md-2'>
    <%= image 'funder-systemsx',:class=>'funder-logo' %>
  </div>
  <div>
    <%= link_to 'SystemsX (SystemsX.ch)', 'http://www.systemsx.ch/', :target => "_blank" %> is the largest public
    research
    initiative in Switzerland. It focuses on a broad topical area
    of basic research with major specialization in systems biology.
  </div>
</div>

<p>
  SEEK development is funded until 2017, and conditionally until 2019. The <%= link_to 'FAIRDOMHub','https://fairdomhub.org',:target=>'_blank' %> is guaranteed to run until 2020.
</p>